description: This cigar features a dark Connecticut Broadleaf Maduro wrapper over a core of Dominican long filler and binder, offering a smooth experience with full flavor and a mild to medium body. As the Maduro version of one of the brand’s longest-running best sellers in our store, it stays true to Fuente’s signature balance and consistency. A reliable classic with just enough richness to keep seasoned smokers coming back.

This cigar has earned its reputation over the past 30 years as a shop staple and one of our top sellers. Wrapped in a toothy Cameroon leaf over Dominican binder and filler, it delivers a mild to medium body with rich, nutty flavors that show exactly why the blend has lasted this long. Familiar, reliable, and always in demand.

Once a limited run, now a regular in the Fuente lineup, the 8-5-8 Sun Grown offers a deeper take on a familiar favorite. The Ecuadorian sun grown wrapper adds a layer of spice and body to the Dominican core, bringing out notes of leather, cedar, cinnamon, and a warm, earthy finish. Medium-bodied and well-balanced, it adds just enough edge without losing its roots.

Originally created out of necessity after a storm wiped out Fuente’s wrapper supply, the Añejo has since earned its place as one of the family’s most celebrated releases. Built with the same aged Dominican filler and binder found in the Opus X line, the blend is finished with a Connecticut Broadleaf Maduro wrapper that spent time resting in cognac barrels. Full-bodied and complex, this cigar offers deep notes of cocoa, baking spice, and a subtle sweetness that sets it apart. Once rare, still revered.

description: Crafted with a Connecticut Broadleaf Maduro wrapper over Dominican binder and filler, the Brevas Royale Maduro offers a medium-bodied profile with notes of coffee, sweetness, and vanilla. This cigar provides a consistent and approachable experience, suitable for both newcomers and seasoned enthusiasts. Its balanced flavor and accessible price point make it a reliable choice for everyday enjoyment.

Wrapped in Cameroon and filled with Dominican tobacco, this cigar leans mild to medium with notes of cedar, toast, and a touch of spice. Built for consistency, it’s an easygoing smoke that fits into just about any time of day. Affordable, dependable, and unmistakably Fuente.

description: This cigar stands as the final blend conceived by Carlos Fuente Sr., inspired by a dream and brought to life through his guidance from afar. Featuring an Ecuadorian Havana wrapper over Dominican binder and filler, it delivers a medium experience with notes of cedar, natural tobacco, and subtle sweetness. The Casa Cuba offers a balanced and nuanced profile, paying homage to traditional Cuban cigar-making techniques.

Crafted with an Ecuadorian Habano wrapper over Dominican binder and filler, this medium-bodied cigar offers a profile of cedar, baking spice, and a touch of citrus. The 6.5 x 42 Lonsdale format allows the wrapper's character to shine, delivering a balanced and nuanced experience. As a personal favorite of Ted's, this cigar exemplifies the harmony between size and flavor.

Handmade in the Dominican Republic, the Arturo Fuente Especiales line offers a medium-bodied profile with notes of cedar, oak, and subtle spice. Wrapped in an Ecuadorian Habano leaf over Dominican binder and filler, these cigars provide a consistent and approachable experience. Available in various sizes, including the Cazadores (6 x 50), Emperador (7 x 52), and Conquistadores (5.5 x 56), the Especiales line delivers quality craftsmanship at an accessible price point.

description: Wrapped in Connecticut Broadleaf and filled with Dominican tobaccos, this cigar offers a rich, medium-bodied profile built on notes of cocoa, cedar, and dark roasted coffee. The Rothschild size delivers a smooth draw and a clean, even burn from start to finish. A dependable Maduro with just enough depth to keep things interesting, it remains a favorite for everyday smoking without ever feeling routine.

Wrapped in a smooth Connecticut Shade leaf, this cigar delivers a mild to medium profile centered on cedar, cream, and a light sweetness. The Dominican filler and binder keep the smoke balanced and easygoing, while the Rothschild size ensures a steady, even burn. Unpretentious and consistent, this cigar has long been a go-to for those who want something mellow but not boring.

Rolled in a Connecticut Shade wrapper over Dominican binder and filler, this torpedo-shaped cigar delivers a mild to medium profile with notes of cedar, cream, and a hint of spice. The tapered head offers a more concentrated draw, bringing out the nuance in the wrapper. A refined option in the Chateau line, suited for those who prefer a classic flavor profile in a more elegant format.

Wrapped in an Ecuadorian Sun Grown leaf over Dominican binder and filler, this cigar delivers a medium-bodied profile with notes of cedar, leather, and a hint of spice. The wrapper adds a touch of natural sweetness, enhancing the overall balance. Consistent construction and a smooth draw make it a reliable choice for those seeking a flavorful yet approachable smoke.

The Royal Salute Maduro comes wrapped in dark Connecticut Broadleaf over Dominican binder and filler, offering a medium-bodied profile with notes of cocoa, espresso, and a hint of spice. Bold in size but easy in character, it’s a natural fit for those who prefer a longer smoke without the intensity to match.

Wrapped in a dark Connecticut Broadleaf over Dominican binder and filler, this Churchill sized cigar offers a medium bodied profile with notes of dark chocolate, licorice, almonds, and wood. Its consistent construction and smooth draw make it a reliable choice for those seeking a rich and balanced smoking experience.

Created by Carlos Fuente Sr. as a personal blend, this cigar represents one of the most respected names in the Fuente family legacy. Featuring a toothy Cameroon wrapper over aged Dominican filler and binder, it offers a medium bodied profile with notes of cedar, cocoa, and sweet spice. The Don Carlos line is a tribute to tradition. Refined, patient, and built with decades of experience behind every leaf.

description: This compact 3½ x 55 cigar delivers a medium to full-bodied profile with notes of Spice, Cedar, White Pepper, and Coffee. The Cameroon wrapper, combined with Dominican binder and filler, offers a rich and balanced experience. A distinctive feature is the dark tobacco circle on the cap, resembling a bull's eye, adding a unique touch to this limited release.

It features the signature Don Carlos blend, a Cameroon wrapper over Dominican tobaccos but with additional age and a deeper, more rounded profile. Medium to full in body, it offers a balanced mix of natural sweetness and gentle spice. A dignified cigar that reflects the legacy of the man it was made for.

The Maduro version of the Chateau line features a dark Connecticut Broadleaf wrapper over Dominican binder and filler, offering a medium-bodied profile with notes of cocoa, earth, and subtle sweetness. Each size in the line maintains the same steady flavor focus, with just enough variation in shape to suit any smoker’s preference. Familiar, approachable, and true to Fuente’s house style, this line remains a dependable go to for those who enjoy a softer take on Maduro.

Wrapped in a golden Connecticut Shade leaf over Dominican binder and filler, the Chateau Natural line delivers a mild to medium bodied profile with notes of cream, cedar, and a touch of sweetness. Whether in the Rothschild, Churchill, or larger Double Chateau format, the blend stays consistent, smooth, balanced, and unmistakably Fuente. A reliable choice for those who enjoy a classic Connecticut without sacrificing character.

description:
The Partagás y Nada Más is a medium-bodied cigar that delivers refined character and classic Cuban-inspired flavor. True to its name, which means "Partagás and nothing more," this cigar focuses on balance, tradition, and pure tobacco enjoyment. Expect notes of earth, cedar, and black pepper with a hint of sweetness that lingers just enough to keep each draw interesting. Smooth in strength but rich in flavor, it is ideal for those who enjoy complexity without overwhelming intensity.
Perfect for seasoned smokers seeking subtlety or newcomers ready to explore the world of premium cigars. This is Partagás in its purest form.

The Gran Habano Habano No 3 is a medium-bodied cigar crafted with a unique blend of Nicaraguan, Mexican, and Costa Rican tobaccos. Wrapped in a smooth Habano leaf, it delivers a well-balanced profile with notes of cedar, spice, roasted coffee, and toasted nuts. Rich in flavor yet approachable, this cigar is a standout choice for smokers who appreciate complexity without overwhelming strength.
This year’s Father’s Day cigar is sweet, spicy, and just a little mischievous, just like Dad. Notes of vanilla, oak, and warm spice shine through, no matter which end you light.

Two masters, one blend. This cigar delivers a bold, refined profile with notes of toasted oak, baking spice, and a subtle molasses sweetness. It’s a meeting of minds and the result is nothing short of exceptional

The Deadwood Dominicana is a fresh face in Drew Estate's Deadwood lineup, bringing a Dominican twist to the brand's signature style. Wrapped in a silky Ecuadorian Connecticut-seed leaf, it features a Mexican San Andrés binder and a core of Dominican Criollo '98 filler tobaccos from La Canela, courtesy of José Mendez & Co.

description: The latest addition to Hoyo's core lineup, the Shade, is a Honduran puro crafted entirely from Honduran tobaccos. It features a shade grown wrapper cultivated in Honduras, paired with Honduran binder and filler, delivering a mellow to medium-bodied profile.

To mark three decades of craftsmanship, Litto and Ines Gomez have introduced the La Flor Dominicana 30th Anniversary cigar, a limited-edition release that embodies the brand's dedication to quality and innovation. Handcrafted at Tabacalera La Flor S.A. in the Dominican Republic, this cigar features an Ecuadorian Sumatra wrapper, a rare aged Dominican binder from Cotuí, and fillers from La Canela. 

Measuring 6 ½ x 58, the cigar is presented in LFD's signature box-pressed Chisel shape, a unique wedge-shaped figurado. Each cigar is adorned with three bands, including a footband marked "30 Years" and a main band featuring a pink tobacco flower, symbolizing the company's name, "The Dominican Flower."

Limited to only 2,000 humidors, each containing 60 cigars, this release is a collector's item. The humidors themselves were crafted at La Flor Dominicana's box factory in the Dominican Republic, featuring an image of Litto and Ines on horseback in one of their tobacco fields.

The Foundation Aksum Maduro is a medium to full-bodied cigar crafted by Nick Melillo of Foundation Cigars. This blend features a dark Ecuadorian Sumatra-seed wrapper, a USA Connecticut Broadleaf binder, and Nicaraguan fillers from Estelí and Jalapa. Handmade at AJ Fernandez’s Tabacalera Fernandez factory in Nicaragua, the Aksum Maduro offers a refined smoking experience.
Previously known as Metapa, the Aksum Maduro pays homage to the ancient Aksumite Kingdom, believed to be the resting place of the Ark of the Covenant. The cigar’s band features an image of Ras Makonnen, father of Haile Selassie, aligning with Foundation's tradition of incorporating historical and cultural themes into their branding.

Filler: Nicaraguan, Dominican, US Broadleaf, Mexican San Andres
description: The Chillin' Moose by Foundry Tobacco Co. is a medium-bodied cigar that offers a complex blend of tobaccos from five countries. It features a Connecticut Habano Rosado wrapper, an Ecuadorian Sumatra binder, and a filler blend of Nicaraguan, Dominican, U.S. Broadleaf, and Mexican San Andrés tobaccos

The Medulla Maduro takes everything people loved about the original and wraps it in a rich San Andrés Maduro leaf. Rolled at CLE’s factory in Honduras, this cigar stays true to its roots with bold Honduran Corojo filler and binder. The maduro wrapper adds a deeper sweetness and a touch of spice, bringing out notes of dark chocolate, leather, espresso, earth, and black pepper.

The Eiroa Jamastran is a bold showcase of Honduran craftsmanship, built entirely from tobaccos grown in the Jamastran Valley. This puro offers a clean, focused expression of the Corojo leaf that put Christian Eiroa’s name on the map.

If you want to taste what Honduran tobacco can do on its own, this is the benchmark.

A rare annual release from Arturo Fuente’s Unnamed Reserve series, the 2021 edition comes in a 5 ¾ by 48 corona gorda that was rolled in 2016 and released five years later. It features a sun grown Rosado wrapper over Dominican binder and filler, all produced at Tabacalera A. Fuente y Cia. Only 1,000 boxes of 20 were made.
This cigar shows off classic Fuente craftsmanship with a smooth draw, even burn, and refined construction. Each stick comes in cellophane and a cedar sleeve marked ProduXion 2016, nodding to the early aging that sets this release apart.
Ideal for collectors or anyone who appreciates pedigree, patience, and a quiet sense of excellence.

The fourth release in the Essence Series, the Essence Connecticut brings a mellow and elegant character to the E.P. Carrillo lineup. It features an Ecuadorian Connecticut wrapper, a Honduran Criollo 98 binder, and a blend of Honduran and Dominican fillers. The result is a smooth and balanced cigar with notes of cream, hay, light pepper, and subtle almond.
Rolled at Agroindustrias Diadema in Honduras, it offers a refined draw and clean finish that make it a perfect pick for those who enjoy Connecticut cigars with a little more depth. Available in Robusto, and Toro sizes, each in 24-count boxes.

The E.P. Carrillo Endure is a return to tradition with a rare Meerapfel-grown Cameroon wrapper that hasn’t been featured in a Perez-Carrillo blend for decades. This is a cigar built on legacy, combining a smooth and flavorful exterior with a Nicaraguan core that brings both strength and finesse.
Medium to full in body, it offers natural sweetness, floral touches, baking spice, and earthy depth, rounded out by a peppery finish and just a hint of nuttiness. Each puff tells a story of resilience and craftsmanship.
Rolled at Tabacalera La Alianza in the Dominican Republic, the Endure is available in box-pressed Robusto and Toro sizes, both packaged in 10-count boxes. A Corona Gorda is set to join the line soon.

Volition America by Gurkha is a patriotic cigar line crafted in partnership with the Folds of Honor Foundation. Each 6x54 Toro comes in one of three blends—Maduro, Habano, or Connecticut—offering options from bold to mild. The cigars are made in Nicaragua with a Nicaraguan binder and a mix of Nicaraguan and Dominican fillers. Every box of 13 cigars symbolizes the 13 folds of the American flag, and 13% of proceeds go toward educational scholarships for families of fallen or disabled military members and first responders.

Volition America by Gurkha is a patriotic cigar line crafted in partnership with the Folds of Honor Foundation. Each 6x54 Toro comes in one of three blends—Maduro, Habano, or Connecticut—offering options from bold to mild. The cigars are made in Nicaragua with a Nicaraguan binder and a mix of Nicaraguan and Dominican fillers. Every box of 13 cigars symbolizes the 13 folds of the American flag, and 13% of proceeds go toward educational scholarships for families of fallen or disabled military members and first responders.

Marking ten years since the original New World debuted, the Decenio is A.J. Fernandez’s way of celebrating the line that helped put his name on the map. Made at the San Lotano factory in Ocotál, Nicaragua, this anniversary blend brings refinement without losing the punch that New World fans expect.
The flavor profile leans rich and savory. Expect notes of dark chocolate, espresso, and black pepper, layered over hints of mesquite and a tangy sweetness that lingers. The result is a balanced, complex smoke that stays interesting from first light to final inch.

Filler: Nicaraguan Esteli, Honduran La Entrada, Dominican Piloto & Andullo, Cyprian Latakia
description: Crafted in partnership with legendary Danish brand Peter Stokkebye, CAO Stock captures the Scandinavian spirit. Blending oak-cured Cyprian pipe tobacco with a complex Andullo-aged Dominican leaf, CAO Stock delivers a smoking experience to match CAO's quest for rare and unique tobaccos.

Crafted in collaboration with A.J. Fernandez, Wabi Sabi is a limited-edition offshoot of the original Kintsugi line. It’s rolled in Nicaragua and offered in a single 6 x 52 toro,  boxed in runs of just 1,500 so when it’s gone, it’s gone. Inspired by the Japanese concept of Wabi Sabi, finding beauty in imperfection, this cigar isn’t about chasing perfection. It’s about honoring character, balance, and craftsmanship.
A worthy addition for collectors and regulars alike.
